vulnerability.name: USN-3216-2
vulnerability.description: USN-3216-1 fixed vulnerabilities in Firefox. The update resulted in a startup crash when Firefox is used with XRDP. This update fixes the problem.  We apologize for the inconvenience.  Original advisory details:   Multiple security issues were discovered in Firefox. If a user were  tricked in to opening a specially crafted website, an attacker could  potentially exploit these to bypass same origin restrictions, obtain  sensitive information, spoof the addressbar, spoof the print dialog,  cause a denial of service via application crash or hang, or execute  arbitrary code. (CVE-2017-5398, CVE-2017-5399, CVE-2017-5400,  CVE-2017-5401, CVE-2017-5402, CVE-2017-5403, CVE-2017-5404, CVE-2017-5405,  CVE-2017-5406, CVE-2017-5407, CVE-2017-5408, CVE-2017-5410, CVE-2017-5412,  CVE-2017-5413, CVE-2017-5414, CVE-2017-5415, CVE-2017-5416, CVE-2017-5417,  CVE-2017-5418, CVE-2017-5419, CVE-2017-5420, CVE-2017-5421, CVE-2017-5422,  CVE-2017-5426, CVE-2017-5427)

statements.status_notes: USN-3216-1 introduced a regression in Firefox.
